{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17502689","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17502689"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T10:48:38+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T10:48:38+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1889"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"1889","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/1889"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.02,0.36,0.53,0.03,0.06]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1889"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"96879"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"1889","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/1889"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1889"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"79494"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"3"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"4955"},{"type":"tags","id":"4970"},{"type":"tags","id":"8088"},{"type":"tags","id":"8161"},{"type":"tags","id":"11629"},{"type":"tags","id":"11644"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"7225"},{"type":"contributions","id":"7308"},{"type":"contributions","id":"29619"},{"type":"contributions","id":"33173"},{"type":"contributions","id":"39248"},{"type":"contributions","id":"42420"},{"type":"contributions","id":"45071"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"96879","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/96879"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 45-year old man presents to his GP for an annual health check. He is generally well, and his history reveals regular alcohol consumption of 3-4 standard drinks most days of the week and a 20 pack year of smoking. He is a tradesman and self-reports regular work under the sun, as well as a brother who has been diagnosed with melanoma. On examination his shirt is lifted and the following is observed (Image)\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following physical signs is present?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Pectus excavatum","Bilateral gynaecomastia","Accessory nipples","Seborrhoeic keratosis","Pigmented lesion suspicious for melanoma"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EWhilst not obvious at first, \u003Cstrong\u003Eaccessory nipples \u003C/strong\u003Ecan be seen. Here is a closer view of one of them (see image attached). Their bilaterality and position (in the milk lines) should make the diagnosis more apparent.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAccessory nipples (also known as supernumary nipples) are found in up to 6% of the population and are present at birth. These are formed early in embryonic development as a result of a failure of mammary ridges along the two vertical milk lines fail to regress. These milk lines span vertically, passing from the axilla, through the nipples and down to the groin - up to 95% of accessory nipples occur along this line however 5% can be found outside the milk lines.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn clinical presentation, accessory nipples are generally benign but may enlarge during puberty or become tender premenstrually and lactate.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA \u003Cstrong\u003Emelanocytic naevus \u003C/strong\u003E(formed by proliferation of melanocytes)\u003Cstrong\u003E \u003C/strong\u003Eand \u003Cstrong\u003Eseborrhoeic keratosis \u003C/strong\u003E(formed by proliferation of keratinocytes) are both common benign pigmented skin lesions that would present as a dark and elevated spot on the skin.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EGynaecomastia\u003C/strong\u003E is a swelling of male breast tissue around the nipples due to low levels of testosterone or increased oestrogen, seen pathologically in conditions such as liver cirrhosis. However, there would not be a pigmented lesion as a result of this. Perhaps this patient\u0027s right breast is slightly enlarged, but the left is normal.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPectus excavatum\u003C/strong\u003E (also known as funnel chest) is caused by a deformity in the position of the sternum, causing protrusion inwards into the thorax forming a depression.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Accessory nipples are benign congenital malformations leading to additional nipples generally along the vertical milk lines."],"references":["Zheng, K., \u0026 Oakley, A. (2015). Supernumerary nipple. Retrieved from https://dermnetnz.org/topics/supernumerary-nipple"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"79494"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1889"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"21688"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"17794"}]}}},{"type":"media","id":"21688","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/21688"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/PWTkVuQZXLAouM0FNEpC776IsKytHW.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/PWTkVuQZXLAouM0FNEpC776IsKytHW.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":587,"height":440}},{"type":"media","id":"17794","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/17794"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/cebcbb93-ff33-48dc-aacb-e04ae906ee4f.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/cebcbb93-ff33-48dc-aacb-e04ae906ee4f.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":800,"height":600}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"79494","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/79494"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-04-03T10:52:26+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-04-03T10:53:31+10:30